>>> Check the Default Root Directory (/var/www/html/)
    cd /var/www/html/
    ls

>>> Check for WordPress Files in the Root Directory
    cd /
    ls

>>> Use find Command to Locate WordPress Files
    sudo find / -maxdepth 1 -name "wp-config.php"

>>> Check the Web Server Configuration (Apache or Nginx):
    * For Apache, check the DocumentRoot in the configuration file:
    cat /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default.conf | grep DocumentRoot

    * For Nginx, check the root directive:
    cat /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default | grep root

>>> Check for the Presence of WordPress-Specific Files:
    ls -l /
